# Logic:
```
Go backward from the end of num (the least significant digit) 
while num still has unprocessed digits or k still has unprocessed digits:
    get k's lowest digit 
    update k (k = 0 would be fine)
    
    # add up the current sum for the current digit
    if (no digit to use in num): no need to add from num 
    else: add up the current sum for the current digit, decrement the index in num
    
    get carry
    insert to the sum list
    
if (carry == 1): insert at sum list's head
```
# Caveats:
Start from the least significant digit in num (go backward), consider carry, what if k's len is longer/shorter, use linkedlist.addFirst()

[0]
23

# Complexity:
Time: O(max(num.length, num of digits in k))

Space: O(max(num.length, num of digits in k)) if we consider the output list; otherwise O(1)

# Code:
```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        LinkedList<Integer> sum = new LinkedList<>();
        int index = num.length - 1;
        int carry = 0;
        while (index >= 0 || k != 0) {
            int curDigit = k % 10;
            k = k / 10;
            
            if (index == -1) {
               curDigit += carry; 
            } else {
                curDigit += num[index--] + carry;
            }
            carry = curDigit / 10;
            sum.addFirst(curDigit % 10);
        }
        if (carry == 1) {
            sum.addFirst(1);
        }
        return sum;
    }
}
```

# Logic:
```
traverse from the left to find matchPos (the closest match on the current index's left)
- update for each index in s

traverse from the right (the closest match on the current index's right)
no need to update the elements after the matchPos, because they have no match on the right
- update for each index in s
```

s = "loveleetcode", c = "e"
It is guaranteed that c occurs at least once in s.

"aaba"
"b"

# Complexity:
Time: O(2n) -> O(n), n is the length of S
Space: O(1) - if we do not consider the output array

# Code:
```
class Solution {
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c) {
        int[] dist = new int[s.length()];
        int matchPos = -s.length(); // the closest c position
        // traverse from the left to find matchPos (the closest match on the current index's left)
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                matchPos = i;
            }
            dist[i] = i - matchPos;
        }
        // traverse from the right (the closest match on the current index's right)
        // no need to update the elements after the matchPos, because they have no match on the right
        for (int i = matchPos - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == c) {
                matchPos = i;
            }
            dist[i] = Math.min(matchPos - i, dist[i]);
        }
        return dist;
    }
}
```

