## æ€è·¯
First Idea is to convert the array into Integer, then  sum up the array and k, then convert into desire result format.

But when array size gets larger, it is easy to get overflow when converting into integer.

Then we need to go through the long way, adding bits from least significant to most significant, 
## å…³é”®ç‚¹

-  

## ä»£ç 

- è¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒï¼šJava

Java Code:

```Java

class Solution {
    public List<Integer> addToArrayForm(int[] num, int k) {
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();

        int carry = 0;
        int numindex = num.length -1;
        
        while(numindex >=0 || k > 0 ){
            int nums = numindex >=0 ? num[numindex] : 0;
            int results = k > 0 ? k % 10 : 0;
                                                      
            int tempval = results + nums + carry;
            int remainder = tempval % 10;
            
            carry = tempval / 10;
            
            result.add(0, remainder);
            numindex--;
            k /=10;
        }
        
        if(carry > 0){
            result.add(0, carry);
        }
        
        return result;
    }
}

```


